title: Photonuclear Reactions With Deuteron Emission.

x4freetext: PHOTONUCLEAR REACTIONS WITH DEUTERON EMISSION.

x4codes.hlp: Fiziko-Tekhnicheskii Inst. Ioffe, Leningrad+Gatchina, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics
Fiziko-Tekhnicheskii Inst. Ioffe, Leningrad+Gatchina, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics

x4freetext: STATISTICAL ERRORS
CORRECTED BY V.VARLAMOV                   VM
THE PAPER DESCRIBES PHOTOREACTIONS INDUCED BY
BREMSSTRAHLUNG WITH DIFFERENT VALUES OF EG-MAX
FROM 30 MEV TO 90 MEV AND RESULTING IN THE EMISSION
OF DEUTERONS IN A BROAD ENERGY INTERVAL. THE RELATIVE
PHOTODEUTERON YIELD WAS MEASURED AS FUNCTION OF THE
NUCLEAR MASS NUMBER AND THE PARTICLE ENERGY FOR A
FIXED VALUE OF EG-MAX AND ALSO AS FUNCTION OF
EG-MAX. THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF THE
PHOTODEUTERONS AND THE EXCITATION FUNCTION FOR THE
(G,D) REACTION WERE STUDIED. CONSIDERATION IS
GIVEN TO SOME POSSIBLE MECHANISM OF THE REACTION
WITH PHOTODEUTERON EMISSION. IT IS SHOWN THAT THE
CROSS SECTION FOR THE (G,D) REACTION HAS AN APPRECIABLE
MAGNITUDE ONLY FOR G-ENERGIES EXCEEDING THE ENERGY
THRESHOLD OF THE REACTION WITH THE EMISSION OF A
SINGLE DEUTERON BY APPROXIMATELY THE NUCLEON BINDING
ENERGY IN THE RESIDUAL NUCLEUS.
